    {
      "id": "821bb30308f3db670ea84e3126521dea6cfe1104",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-02-28 02:02:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nJinshan, could you please expand the commit comment further with details of what kind of performance regression was seen, under what kind of test load, how many clients, how much data written, etc. I think LLNL needs this patch on their nodes or they run out of memory (i.e. their nodes can dirty memory very quickly compared to the size of RAM), and I've also read similar reports from other sites due to the difficulty in freeing Lustre page cache on the clients. \n\nIt would be good to know if this problem is still present after your other patches, and if yes why the accounting is slowing things down. Is it because of the low dirty limit (1/4 of RAM vs. the current 3/4 of RAM dirty limit) or because of extra server-side sync, or something else?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
